snippet.textDisplay: Avery is TOXIC. He doesn't seem it, he is! Acting as if he could've had something planned. Guys like that love isolating women from their friends and family, just saying. It has been so many red flags since he first entered the show and nobody is saying this to be rude but because as fans we genuinely care for Lily, and what he has demonstrated is that he considers her to be his subordinate. I am the same age as Lily and have been with my man for 9 years. If I were to go on a trip with my mom and sister...I could be telling him the day of...he would make sure we're safe, get excited for me, tell us to have fun and to call him as soon as we land, check-in, etc to make sure I'm safe. After that, he wouldn't bombard me and allow me to enjoy myself. This dude has been with her for not even a minute and is calling a trip with her MOTHER, SISTERS, AND NIECE A THOT TRIP! And she feels as though she should have asked permission. To a man who hasn't put a ring on your finger?? You can talk about marriage with someone until u are blue in the face, a real man will PROVE he's even worthy of your love...to not just you but your family!  Someone toxic will try and isolate you from them and make you feel guilty. I've witnessed this first hand with friends and loved ones and Avery has many red flags. I truly hope Lily realizes this sooner than later because she's way too beautiful, kind, and smart to be with someone like that. When I saw he didn't take the time to shake Rick's hand and introduce himself when he first met him that was all that I needed to hear to know he was a scrub.
